men with guns ( spanish : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) is a 1997 american drama film written and directed by john sayles and starring federico luppi , damián delgado , damián &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and mandy patinkin . the executive producers were lou gonda and jody patton . set in an unnamed latin american country , it is the story of one man 's discovery of what actually happened in the political history of his nation as well as his students . it was filmed in mexico and most of the crew were mexican .